AB  - Over the past few decades, Deep Learning (DL), which is a subpart of Machine Learning (ML), has gained recognition as the dominant technique in diverse domains such as Computer Vision, Natural Language Processing, and Image Recognition. However, despite the exceptional performance of DL models, they are often referred to as of “Black Box“ nature, due to their limited ability to explain the decisions. This has led to a need for explainability of DL models. Therefore to address this issue of lack of explainability in DL models, Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI) techniques have been improving in recent era. Unlike DL, XAI has the ability to provide both decision-making and model explanations for data. This research review comprises articles that utilize XAI techniques for image classification tasks. The purpose of this paper is to showcase the utility of the most recent XAI techniques employed in Image Classification Models (ICM). This paper will assist researchers to develop a better intepretation of XAI techniques for image classification as well as related challenges and future research directions.
