AB  - Artificial Intelligence (AI) methods are often applied as black-box solvers for engineering problem solving. While AI methods such as Neural Networks (NNs) can inherently predict non-linearly, statistical regression methods tend to explain impact and correlations better. Recently, EXplainable AI (XAI) methods have been developed to bridge this gap. Results from the BISON computational code validation case of the EBR II X 430 experiment were used to develop XAI models for predicting peak fuel temperatures and cladding radial dilation. Models are compared, and post-hoc analysis of the results are performed to show the capabilities of XAI methods for developing reliable and robust AI models. The best model predictions for each case produced an r2 value above 0.98. Areas of weak prediction and memorization are examined based on high-impact features. © 2023 American Nuclear Society, Incorporated.
