AB  - This chapter introduces methods for achieving an example-based explanation of interpreting the behaviors of black box machine learning models and identifying the characteristics of sample data. These methods help in building a better mental model of model behavior by selecting and showing other samples from a training set to explain the prediction results of a sample of interest. Moreover, practitioners and researchers can utilize methods to identify influential examples or detect mislabeled samples. To properly evaluate samples when selecting appropriate examples, this chapter introduces six methods categorized into similarity- and influence-based methods according to their applied measures. A simple binary classification and the fashion-MNIST problem are also covered to help better understand example-based explanation methods. © 2022 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
