AB  - This chapter elaborates on some key ideas and studies designed to provide post-hoc explanations-by-example to the problem of explaining the predictions of black-box deep-learning systems (the so-called XAI problem). With a focus on image and time series data we review several recent explanation strategies – using factual, counterfactual, and semifactual explanations – for Deep Learners. Several novel evaluations of these methods are reported showing how well these methods work, along with representative outputs that are produced. The chapter also profiles the user studies being carried out on these methods, discussing the pitfalls that arise and results found. © 2023 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
